 <div class="table-wrap-foot">
  <p>
   <span class="italic">Key</span> Regional climate policy is significantly less ambitious than under global policy coordination. Aggregating the regional policy responses (upper part of the table) to global averages (lower part), gives a carbon price of a quarter of the globally optimal, a carbon budget of 1352 GtC, and peak warming of 4.0 °C which compares favourably with 4.9 °C under business-as-usual but is far above the 2.9 °C under international policy coordination and cooperation
